1
00:00:00,083 --> 00:00:01,450
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,450 --> 00:00:02,783
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:08,650 --> 00:00:09,883
(Episode 37)

4
00:00:10,050 --> 00:00:11,050
It's lit.

5
00:00:13,650 --> 00:00:17,950
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

6
00:00:18,450 --> 00:00:24,050
<i>Happy birthday, dear Team Manager
Happy birthday to you</i>

7
00:00:27,083 --> 00:00:29,083
Shall we blow out the candle together now?

8
00:00:29,350 --> 00:00:31,650
Wait. You should make a wish.

9
00:00:32,450 --> 00:00:33,450
A wish?

10
00:00:44,950 --> 00:00:45,983
Now let's blow it out together.

11
00:00:54,250 --> 00:00:55,750
Happy birthday, Team Manager.

12
00:00:56,050 --> 00:00:57,483
Thank you, Eun Ae.

13
00:00:58,250 --> 00:01:00,750
But can I ask why...

14
00:01:01,350 --> 00:01:03,283
you were in such a bad mood earlier?

15
00:01:04,050 --> 00:01:06,683
Is it because
you shouldn't be celebrating...

16
00:01:09,083 --> 00:01:12,550
Actually,
there's a huge secret about my birth...

17
00:01:13,250 --> 00:01:14,250
What?

18
00:01:15,383 --> 00:01:17,150
I'm kidding. It's a joke.

19
00:01:18,183 --> 00:01:20,450
You scared me.

20
00:01:21,483 --> 00:01:24,483
But were you still at the office
this late?

21
00:01:24,483 --> 00:01:26,250
No, I clocked out,

22
00:01:26,250 --> 00:01:28,350
but I forgot something important
and came back.

23
00:01:28,583 --> 00:01:30,150
What was it?

24
00:01:30,650 --> 00:01:31,950
Just something.

25
00:01:32,950 --> 00:01:33,683
But I think...

26
00:01:35,150 --> 00:01:37,450
I just found it.

27
00:01:38,183 --> 00:01:40,183
Team Manager,

28
00:01:40,450 --> 00:01:41,983
you know I'm kind of slow, right?

29
00:01:42,450 --> 00:01:44,583
Don't beat around the bush.

30
00:01:44,750 --> 00:01:46,750
Could you just say it directly?

31
00:01:47,150 --> 00:01:49,483
I have no idea what you're saying.

32
00:01:50,083 --> 00:01:53,550
Are you scolding me right now?
It's my birthday, you know.

33
00:01:53,983 --> 00:01:55,950
Nope. It's past midnight.

34
00:01:56,183 --> 00:01:57,750
Your birthday's over. The end.

35
00:01:58,683 --> 00:02:01,450
They say once a late bloomer
gets into something, they go all in.

36
00:02:01,683 --> 00:02:03,150
You just keep outdoing yourself.

37
00:02:05,450 --> 00:02:07,350
Maybe I should have my main character
video-call the male lead too.

38
00:02:08,750 --> 00:02:09,750
I like it.

39
00:02:11,583 --> 00:02:13,683
(Web Novel-Based Webtoon Production
and Licensing Agreement)

40
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:21,750
Crazy Girl.

41
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:25,950
We've had quite a tumultuous history,

42
00:02:27,350 --> 00:02:29,883
but now I really want to get close to you.

43
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:33,283
Please, okay? Crazy Girl.

44
00:02:37,083 --> 00:02:38,250
Want to grab a drink together for once?

45
00:02:39,383 --> 00:02:41,450
Sure, why not?
Don't you have work tomorrow?

46
00:02:42,150 --> 00:02:43,350
Just one drink, then I'll go.

47
00:02:46,183 --> 00:02:47,183
Cheers.

48
00:02:47,550 --> 00:02:48,550
Wait.

49
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:50,750
Cheers.

50
00:02:55,450 --> 00:02:57,283
Congrats.
You signed the official contract, right?

51
00:02:57,850 --> 00:02:59,750
Yeah. Wait a second.

52
00:03:01,550 --> 00:03:02,983
Take a look at the contract.

53
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:05,983
What's the point of checking it now
when you've already signed it?

54
00:03:07,950 --> 00:03:08,983
The novel is good.

55
00:03:10,050 --> 00:03:12,483
You read it? It's really good, isn't it?

56
00:03:12,750 --> 00:03:14,883
It's well-written and well-structured,

57
00:03:15,483 --> 00:03:17,983
and the vivid realism and expertise
really stood out.

58
00:03:18,150 --> 00:03:21,450
Of course.
The writer used to be a medical student.

59
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:22,783
A former med student?

60
00:03:23,383 --> 00:03:26,083
Yeah, she dropped out of med school
and jumped into the web novel scene.

61
00:03:26,083 --> 00:03:28,050
She's a really gutsy, driven writer.

62
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:32,783
I think I'm really lucky,
especially when getting a partner.

63
00:03:33,250 --> 00:03:34,350
Lucky with your partner...

64
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:36,783
Sounds a little personal.

65
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:39,183
There's nothing personal here, okay?

66
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:42,150
If there were even a hint of that,

67
00:03:42,150 --> 00:03:45,183
I'd be fired by the writer on the spot.

68
00:03:46,750 --> 00:03:48,550
She really hates me.

69
00:03:49,150 --> 00:03:50,950
She practically recoils
whenever she sees me.

70
00:03:51,283 --> 00:03:52,883
Why? What's wrong with you?

71
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:57,183
What is this? Seo Seung Ri actually...

72
00:03:57,650 --> 00:03:59,950
seems to be on my side for once.

73
00:04:00,183 --> 00:04:02,083
Do well.
It's an opportunity you barely got,

74
00:04:02,083 --> 00:04:03,350
so make it count.

75
00:04:03,350 --> 00:04:04,883
Of course.

76
00:04:05,650 --> 00:04:06,950
I'm going to shake up...

77
00:04:06,950 --> 00:04:09,450
the entire Korean webtoon industry
with this.

78
00:04:11,583 --> 00:04:14,083
That aside,
you hadn't seemed like yourself lately,

79
00:04:14,850 --> 00:04:16,050
but today, you look better.

80
00:04:16,050 --> 00:04:18,950
What? Not myself? Here we go again.

81
00:04:24,450 --> 00:04:27,350
This is why
you shouldn't indulge kids too much.

82
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:28,750
Go to sleep.

83
00:04:29,550 --> 00:04:30,550
Hey, Seo Seung Ri.

84
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:33,550
Hang in there. You got this.

85
00:04:39,550 --> 00:04:40,550
Dad.

86
00:04:40,783 --> 00:04:42,950
Hey, Seung Ri. Go to sleep.

87
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:44,950
Okay.

88
00:04:47,883 --> 00:04:50,650
He's drinking at this hour?
What's going on?

89
00:05:14,450 --> 00:05:15,550
I'm here, Dad.

90
00:05:16,383 --> 00:05:19,583
I came early so Grandpa wouldn't worry,

91
00:05:20,250 --> 00:05:22,050
but thank you for coming.

92
00:05:22,550 --> 00:05:24,150
You never even met my father.

93
00:05:29,583 --> 00:05:32,550
We blew out the candle together,
but you couldn't have any cake.

94
00:05:32,950 --> 00:05:34,350
I already ate it with my eyes.

95
00:05:34,883 --> 00:05:37,050
I think I'll gain about two kilos
by tomorrow morning.

96
00:05:38,583 --> 00:05:40,683
It's already past 2 a.m.
You should head home.

97
00:05:41,783 --> 00:05:44,283
Thank you. Sleep well, Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

98
00:05:44,550 --> 00:05:45,750
You too, Team Manager.

99
00:05:46,883 --> 00:05:49,350
Wait, what wish did you make earlier?

100
00:05:50,450 --> 00:05:53,750
That our team wins the first round? Or...

101
00:05:53,783 --> 00:05:56,783
If I say it out loud, it won't come true.
It's a secret.

102
00:05:59,250 --> 00:06:00,250
Wait.

103
00:06:00,650 --> 00:06:02,050
You have to make a wish
before blowing out the candles.

104
00:06:12,550 --> 00:06:13,583
What wish did you make?

105
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:17,283
For you and me to live happily together
for a long time.

106
00:06:18,050 --> 00:06:19,950
Until the end of the world.

107
00:06:22,850 --> 00:06:23,850
That's not how it works.

108
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:27,250
Anyway, happy birthday again,
Team Manager.

109
00:06:28,150 --> 00:06:29,150
Thank you.

110
00:06:43,850 --> 00:06:46,850
Dad, it's the first time since that day...

111
00:06:47,950 --> 00:06:51,150
I've felt happy having someone
celebrate my birthday.

112
00:06:54,050 --> 00:06:56,350
I think...

113
00:06:57,150 --> 00:06:58,483
I really like that girl.

114
00:07:11,050 --> 00:07:13,750
Now that the competition is over,
aren't you a bit freer?

115
00:07:14,050 --> 00:07:17,383
What? Yes, for the time being.

116
00:07:17,383 --> 00:07:19,250
Then why do you look like
you pulled an all-nighter?

117
00:07:21,450 --> 00:07:23,350
Eun Nim, did you stay up writing again?

118
00:07:23,450 --> 00:07:24,450
Yes.

119
00:07:24,850 --> 00:07:27,850
She stayed up by choice.
I stayed up because of her.

120
00:07:28,050 --> 00:07:29,383
What do you mean?

121
00:07:30,150 --> 00:07:31,950
Why would you stay up because of me?

122
00:07:31,950 --> 00:07:33,550
Around midnight,

123
00:07:33,550 --> 00:07:35,950
I suddenly heard someone
singing "Happy Birthday" from somewhere,

124
00:07:36,050 --> 00:07:38,983
- Hey!
- It went on all night, all lovey-dovey.

125
00:07:39,150 --> 00:07:40,750
Here, eat this.

126
00:07:41,050 --> 00:07:43,483
You need enough protein
so your writing flows well.

127
00:07:43,850 --> 00:07:46,150
What's wrong with you two?
You're making me dizzy.

128
00:07:47,050 --> 00:07:49,450
Honey, clear some time this weekend.

129
00:07:50,183 --> 00:07:51,550
Time? What for?

130
00:07:51,550 --> 00:07:54,450
The CEO invited us over
for a couples' dinner.

131
00:07:55,083 --> 00:07:57,450
He must be a nice person,

132
00:07:57,750 --> 00:07:59,450
taking care of his employees' families.

133
00:07:59,450 --> 00:08:00,483
I don't mind going.

134
00:08:02,150 --> 00:08:03,783
I didn't tell you yet, did I?

135
00:08:04,350 --> 00:08:05,883
The CEO is my high school classmate.

136
00:08:06,450 --> 00:08:08,650
Another classmate works
in the secretary's office.

137
00:08:08,983 --> 00:08:10,983
So the three families
will have a meal together.

138
00:08:11,050 --> 00:08:12,183
What? Classmate?

139
00:08:13,450 --> 00:08:15,950
So you're working
as your classmate's assistant?

140
00:08:16,550 --> 00:08:18,550
Why are you only telling me this now?

141
00:08:19,250 --> 00:08:20,750
I didn't think
it was necessary to mention.

142
00:08:23,083 --> 00:08:26,050
Sorry. We said no secrets in this family.

143
00:08:26,850 --> 00:08:30,050
Mom, but is it really possible...

144
00:08:30,550 --> 00:08:32,050
for a family
to have absolutely no secrets?

145
00:08:32,850 --> 00:08:34,950
Do you really have no secrets from us?

146
00:08:36,150 --> 00:08:37,150
What?

147
00:08:38,550 --> 00:08:41,483
Right, you two will share a room again.

148
00:08:42,583 --> 00:08:44,383
I've put your room up for rent,
so keep that in mind.

149
00:08:44,650 --> 00:08:45,650
- What?
- What?

150
00:08:46,850 --> 00:08:49,550
What are you talking about?
Why rent my room all of a sudden?

151
00:08:50,683 --> 00:08:52,650
That used to be your brother's room.

152
00:08:53,450 --> 00:08:56,750
You shared a room before he got married.
What's the problem now?

153
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:58,783
No way. Absolutely not.
I'm strongly against this.

154
00:08:59,083 --> 00:09:01,550
Do you know how hard it was for me
to get away from Eun Ae?

155
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:02,850
Me neither, Mom.

156
00:09:02,983 --> 00:09:05,950
You have no idea how noisy she is at night
when she writes.

157
00:09:05,950 --> 00:09:07,150
You're one to talk.

158
00:09:07,150 --> 00:09:08,950
These days,
you and that team manager or whoever...

159
00:09:09,683 --> 00:09:10,683
Be quiet.

160
00:09:10,850 --> 00:09:14,650
We're on a tight budget from here on out.

161
00:09:14,983 --> 00:09:17,983
Starting this month, you'll all contribute
to living expenses, so be ready.

162
00:09:18,183 --> 00:09:20,483
Dad, stop Mom.

163
00:09:20,950 --> 00:09:23,150
We didn't discuss this.
This is a dictatorship!

164
00:09:23,783 --> 00:09:25,750
It's already out of my hands.

165
00:09:25,950 --> 00:09:29,150
If you don't like it,
move out and live on your own.

166
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:32,483
Once we find a tenant,
move your things out right away.

167
00:09:32,650 --> 00:09:34,450
- Mom.
- Mom.

168
00:09:37,183 --> 00:09:38,183
Here.

169
00:09:43,450 --> 00:09:44,583
Father, you know...

170
00:09:45,550 --> 00:09:47,983
today is the day the first-round results
are announced, right?

171
00:09:48,250 --> 00:09:49,783
Yes, I know.

172
00:09:50,650 --> 00:09:51,750
I wonder how it turned out.

173
00:09:52,083 --> 00:09:53,750
Of course Min Ho must have won.

174
00:09:54,383 --> 00:09:55,383
Mother.

175
00:09:55,783 --> 00:09:57,850
Well, I heard the judges were...

176
00:09:57,850 --> 00:10:00,450
very favorable toward Min Ho's team.

177
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:04,650
I'll let you know
as soon as the final result is announced.

178
00:10:05,350 --> 00:10:07,283
- I'll get going.
- I'll get going.

179
00:10:07,850 --> 00:10:09,450
All right, take care.

180
00:10:10,050 --> 00:10:11,083
Good work.

181
00:10:11,083 --> 00:10:12,250
- Yes.
- Yes, Mother.

182
00:10:12,450 --> 00:10:15,683
Make sure you tell me first
when the results come out, okay?

183
00:10:16,783 --> 00:10:17,783
That's enough.

184
00:10:21,883 --> 00:10:23,650
CEO Ko, I already started the car.

185
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:26,183
Why? Are you going to drive?

186
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:28,850
You want me to?
I thought you didn't want that.

187
00:10:28,850 --> 00:10:30,083
Why isn't your friend coming?

188
00:10:30,350 --> 00:10:32,583
Isn't the executive assistant
supposed to drive too?

189
00:10:32,783 --> 00:10:34,550
Starting next week. I'll get going.

190
00:10:34,950 --> 00:10:35,983
I'm heading out.

191
00:10:35,983 --> 00:10:37,783
Bonne journée. Have a good day.

192
00:10:41,350 --> 00:10:44,550
Put these flowers in your room today,
Madam.

193
00:10:45,050 --> 00:10:47,450
Thank you. They're beautiful.

194
00:10:48,283 --> 00:10:51,283
Mr. Ju, why do you keep cutting flowers?

195
00:10:51,483 --> 00:10:52,950
They're living things too.

196
00:10:52,950 --> 00:10:54,650
You don't understand.

197
00:10:55,150 --> 00:10:57,250
If flowers grow too densely,

198
00:10:57,383 --> 00:10:59,383
they don't get enough light or airflow,

199
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:03,283
so trimming them helps them grow better.

200
00:11:03,283 --> 00:11:06,483
I see.
It must be nice to be so knowledgeable.

201
00:11:09,550 --> 00:11:12,283
Chairman, Gyeol...

202
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:16,350
seemed to have gone somewhere
after the memorial last night.

203
00:11:18,350 --> 00:11:19,350
What?

204
00:11:20,350 --> 00:11:22,050
I think it was around 4 a.m.

205
00:11:22,350 --> 00:11:25,150
I woke up early
and went out to the garden.

206
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:28,250
That's when he came in.
Then, about an hour later,

207
00:11:28,250 --> 00:11:31,983
he changed clothes and went out again,
saying he was going to work.

208
00:11:33,383 --> 00:11:34,950
What should we do?

209
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:38,450
He just can't seem to settle here.

210
00:11:42,883 --> 00:11:44,583
(Kangsu Construction)

211
00:11:46,983 --> 00:11:48,050
All right.

212
00:11:48,483 --> 00:11:49,883
Please sit down.

213
00:11:50,450 --> 00:11:53,150
I'm not that authoritarian, so sit down.

214
00:11:55,183 --> 00:11:56,950
- Mr. Cho.
- Yes, here.

215
00:11:58,450 --> 00:11:59,583
I will now announce...

216
00:11:59,850 --> 00:12:03,050
the final results
of the first round of the competition.

217
00:12:04,583 --> 00:12:05,850
For fairness,

218
00:12:06,450 --> 00:12:08,850
the external panel tallied...

219
00:12:09,250 --> 00:12:11,250
the judges' scores,

220
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:14,483
so even I don't know the final result yet.

221
00:12:15,350 --> 00:12:16,383
Now...

222
00:12:21,183 --> 00:12:24,350
Now, the winning team
of the first round...

223
00:12:29,450 --> 00:12:31,750
will be revealed in 60 seconds!

224
00:12:38,450 --> 00:12:39,450
This is fun.

225
00:12:40,383 --> 00:12:42,383
All right, here we go.

226
00:12:43,650 --> 00:12:45,050
The final score...

227
00:12:47,983 --> 00:12:50,750
is 58 to 42.

228
00:12:54,450 --> 00:12:55,683
Team One wins.

229
00:13:05,383 --> 00:13:08,650
Team Two did well in their own way,

230
00:13:08,650 --> 00:13:09,850
but it's a bit unfortunate...

231
00:13:10,350 --> 00:13:12,450
they didn't meet expectations,
Team Manager Ko.

232
00:13:12,883 --> 00:13:16,283
Not at all. Congratulations, Chief.
And to your team as well.

233
00:13:16,750 --> 00:13:19,983
It's a bit early for congratulations,
but thank you.

234
00:13:20,783 --> 00:13:24,550
All right, I hope both teams continue
to do their best in the remaining rounds.

235
00:13:25,150 --> 00:13:26,750
- Now.
- Yes.

236
00:13:26,950 --> 00:13:28,783
Mr. Cho, let's go.

237
00:13:29,450 --> 00:13:30,450
Yes, sir.

238
00:13:36,350 --> 00:13:38,183
Manager Seo, can we talk?

239
00:13:38,950 --> 00:13:39,950
Yes, Chief.

240
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:45,050
I'm sorry, Team Manager.
We should've worked harder.

241
00:13:45,150 --> 00:13:48,850
No, we got a much better score
than I expected.

242
00:13:49,050 --> 00:13:50,050
It's thanks to both of you.

243
00:13:50,183 --> 00:13:52,150
Team Manager,
I uploaded the Joy implementation plan...

244
00:13:52,150 --> 00:13:54,750
to the group chat. Please check it.
You too, Assistant Manager.

245
00:13:55,850 --> 00:13:56,850
Okay.

246
00:14:00,083 --> 00:14:01,983
Now, time to keep your promise.

247
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:04,950
What? What promise?

248
00:14:05,250 --> 00:14:06,450
Did you forget already?

249
00:14:07,150 --> 00:14:09,750
You said you'd grant my wish
if we won this round.

250
00:14:11,383 --> 00:14:14,250
Yes, I remember. What is it?

251
00:14:14,950 --> 00:14:17,950
You said it'd be something small,
so not to feel pressured.

252
00:14:19,950 --> 00:14:21,850
Accompany me
on a field assignment this afternoon.

253
00:14:22,450 --> 00:14:25,750
What? Your wish is to go out and work?

254
00:14:26,083 --> 00:14:27,650
Yes. Why? Is that a problem?

255
00:14:28,683 --> 00:14:31,383
I want to check out a few places
for our retirement community project.

256
00:14:32,283 --> 00:14:34,750
I'm planning to leave around noon,
so be ready.

257
00:14:35,850 --> 00:14:37,450
Yes, I'll be ready.

258
00:14:44,083 --> 00:14:46,850
I'm telling you, this external panel...

259
00:14:46,850 --> 00:14:48,750
is more fair than I expected.

260
00:14:49,650 --> 00:14:50,683
What do you think, Mr. Cho?

261
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:55,450
I'm not familiar with the details,
so I don't really have anything to say.

262
00:14:55,683 --> 00:14:56,683
Right.

263
00:14:57,650 --> 00:14:59,550
I mean, Team Manager Ko...

264
00:15:00,150 --> 00:15:02,150
He really thinks he's something.

265
00:15:03,050 --> 00:15:05,250
He got a few international awards,
and now he's so arrogant.

266
00:15:06,183 --> 00:15:08,250
This isn't
some public service organization.

267
00:15:08,250 --> 00:15:11,183
If he wants to make art,
he should just leave the company.

268
00:15:14,850 --> 00:15:15,850
Why are you looking at me like that?

269
00:15:17,250 --> 00:15:19,250
You're one of the judges too.

270
00:15:20,050 --> 00:15:21,750
Isn't that a bit biased?

271
00:15:22,183 --> 00:15:26,050
When was I? I'm completely neutral.

272
00:15:26,450 --> 00:15:27,450
Purely fair.

273
00:15:30,483 --> 00:15:33,650
Right, your daughter's on Team Two,
isn't she?

274
00:15:33,650 --> 00:15:34,750
That explains it.

275
00:15:35,150 --> 00:15:38,750
Well, if you look at it that way,
isn't Team Manager Ko your son?

276
00:15:39,083 --> 00:15:40,083
What?

277
00:15:40,583 --> 00:15:43,383
Are you saying I'm showing favoritism
between my two sons?

278
00:15:44,883 --> 00:15:45,983
That's not what I meant.

279
00:15:46,650 --> 00:15:48,350
Think before you speak, seriously.

280
00:15:49,083 --> 00:15:52,350
And did you tell your family
about the couples' gathering this weekend?

281
00:15:52,950 --> 00:15:54,950
Yes,
we agreed to attend together that day.

282
00:15:55,183 --> 00:15:56,250
Good, that's great.

283
00:15:56,950 --> 00:15:59,883
Then I'll let Gwon Sik know.

284
00:16:03,250 --> 00:16:05,250
Mr. Seo, it's me.

285
00:16:08,383 --> 00:16:10,650
What's for lunch today?

286
00:16:11,350 --> 00:16:13,250
What do you want to eat?
Just say the word.

287
00:16:15,150 --> 00:16:17,383
Are you treating me differently
now that I signed a contract?

288
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:20,450
Of course.
You finally escaped unemployment.

289
00:16:21,483 --> 00:16:22,583
Want me to give you some money?

290
00:16:22,950 --> 00:16:24,850
Seems like you haven't gotten
any allowance lately.

291
00:16:25,583 --> 00:16:27,550
No, I'm fine.

292
00:16:29,050 --> 00:16:32,050
I got a signing bonus,
and last time Min Ho's mom...

293
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:34,750
gave me quite a bit in exchange
for keeping a secret...

294
00:16:36,250 --> 00:16:39,550
What?
Min Ho's mom paid you to keep a secret?

295
00:16:40,550 --> 00:16:41,550
What secret?

296
00:16:41,950 --> 00:16:43,483
I must be crazy.

297
00:16:44,083 --> 00:16:46,983
I can't tell you.
I already took the money. How can I?

298
00:16:47,183 --> 00:16:50,250
You punk.
Do you want to get hit or just spill it?

299
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:52,983
You're hosting the couples' gathering
at home?

300
00:16:53,450 --> 00:16:55,050
Why? Is that a problem?

301
00:16:55,483 --> 00:16:56,883
It's not that it's a problem,

302
00:16:57,950 --> 00:17:01,783
but Father isn't well,
so inviting guests...

303
00:17:01,983 --> 00:17:04,750
I suggested having it outside too,

304
00:17:05,150 --> 00:17:07,550
but Dae Chi insisted
on keeping it simple at home.

305
00:17:08,450 --> 00:17:09,650
Well, do as you like.

306
00:17:10,550 --> 00:17:13,383
I know Seong Jun well enough.

307
00:17:14,283 --> 00:17:15,483
You don't need to worry about me.

308
00:17:16,083 --> 00:17:18,483
I'm going to take a nap.

309
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:20,750
Yes, go ahead.

310
00:17:23,450 --> 00:17:25,850
Then should we hire a catering chef
for that day?

311
00:17:25,850 --> 00:17:26,983
You might have a hard time.

312
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:28,683
Why would we need a catering chef?

313
00:17:29,383 --> 00:17:31,350
If you're that worried, help out instead.

314
00:17:31,450 --> 00:17:33,250
Would I really be any help?

315
00:17:33,483 --> 00:17:35,883
Jeong Ran and the maid will assist you,

316
00:17:35,883 --> 00:17:37,783
and I'll be in charge
of the party overall,

317
00:17:37,783 --> 00:17:40,550
and busy preparing events as well.

318
00:17:41,150 --> 00:17:43,183
Did you forget Father is ill?

319
00:17:44,150 --> 00:17:47,950
You can just have a quiet meal.
What events?

320
00:17:49,450 --> 00:17:52,350
I understand what you're saying,

321
00:17:52,750 --> 00:17:55,483
but it's to boost Dae Chi's morale
in front of his friends.

322
00:17:55,850 --> 00:17:58,050
Are they children?
Boost his morale with that?

323
00:17:58,550 --> 00:18:03,250
And Jeong Ran is also an invited guest.

324
00:18:03,250 --> 00:18:04,650
How can you make her assist me?

325
00:18:04,650 --> 00:18:07,050
Like she'd listen if you told her not to?

326
00:18:07,383 --> 00:18:09,150
She'll do it anyway.

327
00:18:09,250 --> 00:18:12,250
Yes, I'll take care of everything myself.

328
00:18:13,050 --> 00:18:14,050
Welcome, Jeong Ran.

329
00:18:15,050 --> 00:18:16,183
I'm here, ma'am.

330
00:18:16,350 --> 00:18:19,783
See? I didn't even call her,
and she came on her own.

331
00:18:20,250 --> 00:18:23,250
By the way,
do you even know our door code?

332
00:18:23,883 --> 00:18:25,983
How can you come and go
like it's your own house?

333
00:18:26,483 --> 00:18:27,983
You told me yourself.

334
00:18:28,350 --> 00:18:30,350
You said it was a hassle
to open the door every time,

335
00:18:30,350 --> 00:18:31,683
so I should just punch in the code
and come in.

336
00:18:31,850 --> 00:18:32,883
I did?

337
00:18:33,250 --> 00:18:36,450
You spent all day yesterday
helping with the memorial food,

338
00:18:37,150 --> 00:18:39,150
so why are you here again
instead of resting?

339
00:18:40,050 --> 00:18:43,250
I have something to discuss
with Su Jeong today.

340
00:18:44,250 --> 00:18:45,250
With me?

341
00:18:45,650 --> 00:18:48,050
Then you two talk. I'll head inside.

342
00:18:48,050 --> 00:18:49,250
Yes, ma'am.

343
00:18:52,983 --> 00:18:54,683
Why are you looking at me like that?

344
00:18:54,683 --> 00:18:56,983
Why did you go through my husband's study?

345
00:18:57,750 --> 00:18:59,950
You asked me to prepare a meal,
so why did you go in there?

346
00:19:01,350 --> 00:19:02,850
What do you mean, "go through?"
When did I?

347
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:04,083
What am I, a mole?

348
00:19:05,083 --> 00:19:08,450
Tell me! Why did you go through his study?

349
00:19:08,450 --> 00:19:10,750
What's wrong with you? Seriously.

350
00:19:11,583 --> 00:19:12,683
Just tell me.

351
00:19:12,683 --> 00:19:14,150
- Why are you being like this...
- Seriously.

352
00:19:14,150 --> 00:19:16,150
I didn't go through his study!

353
00:19:16,150 --> 00:19:18,750
The drawers were locked.
How could I even look for anything...

354
00:19:20,850 --> 00:19:22,483
So you admit it.

355
00:19:25,950 --> 00:19:28,950
Here. The money you gave Seung Wu
to keep him quiet.

356
00:19:30,250 --> 00:19:31,883
That kid is ridiculous.

357
00:19:32,150 --> 00:19:34,550
I've known him since he was a kid,

358
00:19:34,950 --> 00:19:37,050
and I just gave some allowance
to an unemployed guy...

359
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:38,183
who lounges in his room all day.

360
00:19:38,183 --> 00:19:41,183
Unemployed? How is Seung Wu unemployed?

361
00:19:41,883 --> 00:19:44,783
He officially signed a contract
as a webtoon artist.

362
00:19:45,850 --> 00:19:48,450
You look like you're about to shoot
laser beams from your eyes.

363
00:19:48,950 --> 00:19:51,183
How scary.

364
00:19:51,550 --> 00:19:53,883
I don't know what you're trying to dig up,

365
00:19:54,550 --> 00:19:56,150
but please stop.

366
00:19:57,350 --> 00:19:59,350
You've changed lately, haven't you?

367
00:20:00,083 --> 00:20:01,850
Is it that real estate lady's influence?

368
00:20:01,850 --> 00:20:02,983
What are you talking about?

369
00:20:03,583 --> 00:20:06,450
It just feels like...

370
00:20:06,450 --> 00:20:07,850
you've started taking me lightly.

371
00:20:09,150 --> 00:20:12,883
You must've forgotten.
I'm CEO Ko Dae Chi's wife.

372
00:20:13,550 --> 00:20:15,183
The wife of the future chairman.

373
00:20:17,350 --> 00:20:19,850
Says who?

374
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:22,450
We'll see about that.

375
00:20:23,483 --> 00:20:24,950
If Dae Chi were truly capable,

376
00:20:25,650 --> 00:20:28,150
why would the Chairman
make his sons compete?

377
00:20:29,550 --> 00:20:30,650
What are you saying right now?

378
00:20:31,050 --> 00:20:33,550
Are you saying Dae Chi isn't fit
to be chairman?

379
00:20:35,283 --> 00:20:36,683
Did you just hear that out loud?

380
00:20:37,350 --> 00:20:39,150
I only thought it to myself.

381
00:20:40,950 --> 00:20:43,383
Unbelievable, seriously.

382
00:20:46,050 --> 00:20:48,983
Feels so refreshing to finally say
what I've been holding in.

383
00:20:49,650 --> 00:20:51,050
You just said something
with your eyes again.

384
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:53,650
Say it. What is it?

385
00:20:53,650 --> 00:20:54,883
Go on, say it!

386
00:20:56,583 --> 00:20:57,683
That felt good.

387
00:20:58,483 --> 00:21:01,850
I can't stand you, seriously.

388
00:21:03,950 --> 00:21:05,150
Honey, what are you doing?

389
00:21:06,050 --> 00:21:08,650
Just calculating bills and stuff.

390
00:21:12,983 --> 00:21:13,983
Are you heading
to the cram school already?

391
00:21:13,983 --> 00:21:15,250
Classes start at four,

392
00:21:15,550 --> 00:21:16,850
but I'm going to pick up Bit Na first.

393
00:21:17,983 --> 00:21:21,450
By the way,
the lease for this place ends next month.

394
00:21:21,450 --> 00:21:22,750
Has the landlord contacted you?

395
00:21:23,083 --> 00:21:24,150
Not yet.

396
00:21:25,583 --> 00:21:27,383
It'll be a problem
if they ask for a higher deposit.

397
00:21:27,483 --> 00:21:28,650
Don't worry too much.

398
00:21:28,650 --> 00:21:31,150
If they do,
we can just find a smaller place.

399
00:21:32,083 --> 00:21:34,183
This place is already small.
We'd move somewhere even smaller?

400
00:21:35,283 --> 00:21:36,783
What, are we moving into a studio?

401
00:21:38,750 --> 00:21:40,650
- Anyway, see you.
- Okay.

402
00:21:46,850 --> 00:21:48,383
How long do we have to live like this?

403
00:21:53,350 --> 00:21:55,550
Hey. What is it at this hour?

404
00:21:57,783 --> 00:21:59,483
I'm basically on vacation at home.

405
00:22:01,250 --> 00:22:02,750
Overseas travel? No thanks.

406
00:22:03,083 --> 00:22:04,750
I'm sick of planes.

407
00:22:04,850 --> 00:22:08,150
I wanted to give you
some good investment information.

408
00:22:08,450 --> 00:22:09,450
Investment info?

409
00:22:09,850 --> 00:22:12,750
Do I look like I have money to invest?

410
00:22:13,050 --> 00:22:16,850
Remember how my mother-in-law
got all that cash?

411
00:22:16,983 --> 00:22:20,050
Money really does make more money.

412
00:22:22,250 --> 00:22:23,350
Anyway, too bad.

413
00:22:24,150 --> 00:22:26,050
You can easily make 20 percent a month.

414
00:22:26,550 --> 00:22:27,550
Really?

415
00:22:29,150 --> 00:22:32,583
Forget it.
I'm already tight on living expenses.

416
00:22:33,650 --> 00:22:37,350
But what kind of investment
gives that kind of return?

417
00:22:38,483 --> 00:22:41,050
Assistant Manager Kim, you checked
the Joy system proposal, right?

418
00:22:41,550 --> 00:22:44,750
Yes, but Team Manager,
are you really okay?

419
00:22:45,050 --> 00:22:47,083
We lost just an hour ago.

420
00:22:47,350 --> 00:22:49,750
Well, I don't think we lost.

421
00:22:50,250 --> 00:22:51,683
We just failed...

422
00:22:51,683 --> 00:22:54,883
To convince the judges.
And the real game...

423
00:22:55,350 --> 00:22:56,483
Starts now.

424
00:22:57,250 --> 00:22:58,950
How do you two get along so well?

425
00:22:59,383 --> 00:23:01,350
It's like you're sharing the same brain.

426
00:23:01,650 --> 00:23:03,283
As if we have enough brains to share.

427
00:23:10,450 --> 00:23:14,050
Ms. Cho Eun Ae,
please explain the Joy system.

428
00:23:14,583 --> 00:23:15,583
Yes.

429
00:23:16,983 --> 00:23:19,983
I'll explain it simply
by drawing on the whiteboard.

430
00:23:21,383 --> 00:23:23,550
This square is the retirement community.

431
00:23:24,050 --> 00:23:26,150
And this is Joy.

432
00:23:26,650 --> 00:23:29,950
Instead of placing Joy
inside the building,

433
00:23:30,350 --> 00:23:33,150
we connect it
to the entire lifestyle data...

434
00:23:33,150 --> 00:23:34,550
of the retirement community.

435
00:23:36,983 --> 00:23:39,183
The problem is, your arrow...

436
00:23:39,183 --> 00:23:39,783
(Me, Team Manager)

437
00:23:39,783 --> 00:23:41,950
Seems like it might be pointing at me...

438
00:23:42,650 --> 00:23:44,083
Like maybe, maybe not.

439
00:23:48,050 --> 00:23:49,050
Why are you laughing?

440
00:23:51,250 --> 00:23:53,683
It's nothing. Please continue, sorry.

441
00:23:54,783 --> 00:23:58,250
When Joy connects people to each other...

442
00:23:59,250 --> 00:24:02,350
Where is your arrow pointing, Ms. Cho?

443
00:24:03,050 --> 00:24:04,350
Well...

444
00:24:09,683 --> 00:24:12,750
Did you inhale laughing gas?
Why do you keep laughing?

445
00:24:14,750 --> 00:24:18,450
I'm sorry. Let's just take...

446
00:24:18,450 --> 00:24:20,583
a ten-minute break. Sorry.

447
00:24:22,250 --> 00:24:23,450
Seriously.

448
00:24:34,850 --> 00:24:36,383
What's got you in such a good mood?

449
00:24:36,983 --> 00:24:39,850
Shouldn't you be a bit down today?

450
00:24:40,550 --> 00:24:43,050
Why? Is there a reason I should be?

451
00:24:43,350 --> 00:24:46,150
You're not worried
about losing the first round?

452
00:24:46,650 --> 00:24:48,350
You seem pretty confident.

453
00:24:48,850 --> 00:24:50,483
Fine, I'll take note of that.

454
00:24:51,950 --> 00:24:54,483
But Ms. Cho Eun Ae is impressive.

455
00:24:54,850 --> 00:24:56,883
How could she change someone like this?

456
00:24:56,950 --> 00:24:59,050
If it's not important, please leave.

457
00:25:04,783 --> 00:25:05,783
Yes, Grandpa.

458
00:25:06,450 --> 00:25:08,550
Come straight home after work.

459
00:25:09,183 --> 00:25:10,550
I have something to tell you.

460
00:25:11,283 --> 00:25:14,783
Yes, understood.
I also have something to tell you.

461
00:25:25,450 --> 00:25:27,883
(Happy birthday
to the most noble team manager!)

462
00:25:41,650 --> 00:25:43,750
What are you doing? We need to head out.

463
00:25:46,150 --> 00:25:47,383
Yes, let's go.

464
00:25:51,850 --> 00:25:53,150
Gyeol had a birthday party?

465
00:25:58,450 --> 00:25:59,450
Enjoy your meal.

466
00:26:02,050 --> 00:26:03,750
Eating is the field assignment?

467
00:26:04,283 --> 00:26:07,450
This is a Michelin three-star
Korean fine dining restaurant.

468
00:26:07,850 --> 00:26:10,750
I'm thinking of bringing this chef
into our retirement community.

469
00:26:11,183 --> 00:26:13,550
Before that,
the person in charge should try the food.

470
00:26:14,350 --> 00:26:16,950
- Let's eat.
- Yes.

471
00:26:22,050 --> 00:26:23,050
How was it?

472
00:26:24,050 --> 00:26:26,850
They didn't just preserve the flavors,
they maximized them.

473
00:26:27,283 --> 00:26:30,050
It's not overwhelming,
and the nutritional balance is excellent.

474
00:26:30,483 --> 00:26:33,350
What if meals like this were provided
as room service every time?

475
00:26:34,050 --> 00:26:36,350
Wouldn't it be incomparable to Team Two?

476
00:26:37,050 --> 00:26:40,783
The two teams have different directions,
so I don't think a comparison works.

477
00:26:40,783 --> 00:26:42,550
Then where would you want to live?

478
00:26:43,083 --> 00:26:44,350
Growing your own garden...

479
00:26:44,350 --> 00:26:46,283
and eating together
in a shared dining hall? Or...

480
00:26:46,283 --> 00:26:50,050
More than where you live,
it's who you live with that matters.

481
00:26:52,883 --> 00:26:54,250
Where's the next place?

482
00:26:54,783 --> 00:26:57,350
You'll see when we get there.

483
00:26:59,383 --> 00:27:03,050
Where did you go after the memorial,
staying out until dawn?

484
00:27:04,350 --> 00:27:05,750
Just to the office for a bit.

485
00:27:06,450 --> 00:27:09,583
Is this house that uncomfortable for you?

486
00:27:10,250 --> 00:27:11,583
No, it's not like that.

487
00:27:12,450 --> 00:27:13,450
Then,

488
00:27:13,883 --> 00:27:16,583
why do you still seem so unsettled?

489
00:27:17,650 --> 00:27:19,483
I'm sorry for worrying you, Grandpa.

490
00:27:21,083 --> 00:27:23,583
Do you feel...

491
00:27:24,050 --> 00:27:27,150
the first-round result was unfair?

492
00:27:27,383 --> 00:27:30,050
No, I expected the result.

493
00:27:30,383 --> 00:27:32,683
I know my approach...

494
00:27:32,683 --> 00:27:34,683
is far from profit-driven.

495
00:27:36,050 --> 00:27:38,783
Do you think all companies...

496
00:27:38,783 --> 00:27:40,250
only pursue profit?

497
00:27:41,383 --> 00:27:42,483
I told you.

498
00:27:43,650 --> 00:27:46,283
If you're convinced it's a good concept,

499
00:27:46,883 --> 00:27:48,450
you should try to persuade them
from a business standpoint.

500
00:27:48,883 --> 00:27:50,550
Yes, I will.

501
00:27:52,350 --> 00:27:55,683
You said you had something to tell me.
Go ahead.

502
00:27:57,350 --> 00:27:59,950
Grandpa, I...

503
00:28:01,683 --> 00:28:02,950
I'm going to move out.

504
00:28:04,983 --> 00:28:07,050
What? Move out?

505
00:28:25,983 --> 00:28:27,450
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
